Be careful with doing a full boil batch; if it is a 5 gallon kit and you have a 6 gallon kettle, the chance of a boilover occurring goes up significantly. I don't plan to start doing full-batch boils until have a 8-gallon or larger kettle.This is based on what I've read so any real-world experience would be appreciated here.The wife and I bottled 2 batches this weekend--a Northern Brewer kit called Caribou Slobber which is a English style session ale. We also bottled a smoked porter. Both were fermented using White Labs WLP006. The Caribou Slobberis going to be quite tasty; I can't wait until these brew are bottle conditioned.I am still trying to figure out how I want t do a pumpkin ale this year; I like te iea of using a Belgian style ale as a base.
