Tribus: Iowa City, IA
Registered: Jan 18, 2001Posts: 2511
Posted: Tue Nov 01, 2011 3:36 pm
asphaltbuffet wrote:Don't know where head has been last couple weeks. Racked my Russian Imperial Stout into the carboy 2 weeks ago for secondary and then promptly forgot about it sitting in kitchen. In regular daylight (no direct sun shining on it, but still...)What did I manage to do here? Should I bother with bottling? Usually my stuff all gets stuck in the nice dark basement until it's ready for the next stage.It's possible it's light struck, though that's a function of the amount of hops you have. Sniff/taste test it. If you detect skunk, it's been struck. If it's struck I wouldn't dump it though, throw some bourbon soaked oak sticks and a couple vanilla beans at it and hide it away for a month or two. You never know how something will mellow out, I've had "mistakes" end up working quite well through neglectaging.
