Bumping this to heap some praise on a new (to me) vendor I used for an order yesterday, Rebel Brewer http://www.rebelbrewer.com/. I haven't received my order yet obviously, but after the phone call I just had I'm suitably impressed with their customer service.I had an idea for a beer that started with a spec sheet from Briess on their new seasonal CaraBrown malt. Looking around Rebel seemed to be the only place that carried it, and their pricing was as good/better than Austin/Northern/More on everything else so figured I'd go ahead and place my entire order with them. I was kind of rushing through my order and using the search engine to find what I wanted quickly. My base malt is going to be Maris Otter so placed 10lbs in the cart along with the rest of my order and clicked purchase. I just got off the phone with the guy packing my order. In my haste I'd apparently ordered Crystal Maris Otter, and when he was packaging things up he thought that looked like my intended base malt and that it looked like a really odd choice so called me to make sure that's what I wanted. I was pretty shocked and said that no, I'd actually meant to order the Crisp Maris Otter, and thanked him profusely for noticing my gaffe.Now I don't expect that to happen when ordering on the internet, I clearly wasn't paying enough attention when shopping, but damn color me impressed by the service. Anyways, a bit of a plug and thanks to them I'll be a happier camper on brew day. yakumo
